      "body": "I agree with Marco it's nice for these lint checks to apply. The thing that's not ideal is just the way the checks are currently applied because they aren't performed until the subtree is updated. One way to improve this might be to extend https://github.com/bitcoin-core/libmultiprocess/pull/253 to run the Bitcoin core lint job in addition to other jobs when libmultiprocess prs are opened to provide earlier feedback. (It could also be good to make Bitcoin core CI code more [modular](https://github.com/bitcoin-core/libmultiprocess/pull/253#pullrequestreview-4007879902) so the checks could be easier to reuse and probably easier to maintain.)",
